Reasoning: 
- cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper proposes a method to reduce the training overhead of establishing an mmWave communication link using a passive radar receiver. Information theory concepts such as achievable rate are also mentioned in the paper. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper deals with establishing communication links between vehicles and roadside units, which falls under the purview of networking and internet architecture. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes a system-level solution to reduce the training overhead of establishing an mmWave communication link. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper deals with communication links that can be used for multimedia applications such as video streaming in vehicles. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security): Although not the main focus of the paper, the proposed method could have implications for security and privacy in vehicular communication networks.
